reviews.text: I thought this was a great restaurant and the food was delicious. They are a little out of the way but the views and food are worth it. Staff were very attentive but not overpowering. Excellent venue for that special occasion. Don’t expect a cheap night though, however the cost is expected for such good quality with a very innovative menu.

My fiancée and I celebrated our 4th anniversary and recent engagement at Alchemy. The ambience was great and we managed to get a table with a view of the story bridge (absolutely stunning at night!). Our waitress, Morgan, made us feel very welcome and was very attentive to us throughout the evening. The food was exceptional! Everything from the presentation to the combination of flavours and textures was beautiful. We want to thank the chef and staff at Alchemy for making our evening such a special one.

Attended as part of a set menu day/business function. Staff presented well and were polite, attentive and helpful. 

Food was adventurous yet basic enough for every tastebud to enjoy. Extensive drinks list to mull over.

And if you were boring and for some reason weren't impressed by the restaurants other great features, the view is always spectacular!
Great quality meals. Great customer service. 11 dollars for still mineral water bottle was a bit much though. My medium rare steak was cooked to perfection. Cocktails were yummy but super small :)

Service from our waitress Lilly was great. French speaking, petite and helpful. The food for me was the disappointment. While the vegetarian menu seemed appealing, my selections from it were underwhelming. The gnocchi were more like pasta shells than any gnocchi I have encountered and not flavoursome either. On the basis of that alone I would have given 3 stars but my colleagues enjoyed their beeftarian dishes so on that basis and the service it gets the 4th star. The location i s good, no doubt. The decor is pleasant.
Love the food here. The best tasting Chinese food I have tasted. The people that work there are so friendly and are always smiling. Keep up the good work !
Outstanding location for delicious chinese food. Visited Sat afternoon. I will be back with my coworkers. Bring your appetite because portions are filling.

This is our go to place for Chinese food.  They even know us by what we order. We think that this place makes some of the best Chinese food for your run of the mill commercial Chinese joints. 
Very pleasant to deal with. Give them a try you will like it.
Quick, consistent, excellent service with a smile. Love them.
Absolutely wonderful food. Quick and fresh. Nothing was reheated or cold. Great portions.

Havana belongs on any foodie's "Note to Self" page during visits to Bar Harbor.  Innovative menu for vegans and meat-lovers alike (rare!) and an inviting wine list to boot.  That they remain open most of the year - even off season - adds to our delight in visiting.  Love this place.
Really lovely little restaurant with a friendly staff.  The food was very good and the beer selection decent.  Although they got both of my beer orders wrong I would definitely go back.

Excellent restaurant. Had the fish of the day and by far was the best fish I've ever had. Portion is a little small and wait times can be long, but it is what it is. A few other patrons had the tapas and they looked excellent as well. Would recommend.

Our experience at Havana is second to none. The service was incredible matched only by the food and drinks. Enrique our server was fantastic. I highly recommend the black bean soup, the empanadas and the farmhouse salad, and the Havana martini is tasty.  Thanks!!

Best paella I've ever eaten - generous helping of perfectly-cooked seafood and the saucy rice was just spot on. But everything we had was delicious anyway. The mashed potatoes with coconut that came with one of the daily specials was just... So good...

The wine list is nuts, apparently one of the largest in the region. They have the little notes in the wine menu to help you choose, and we were really happy with the bottle we had.

And of course, the service was excellent. They open at 5pm but it appears that the live music starts a little later.

DO NOT ORDER FROM THIS PLACE THEY WILL SCAM YOU! 
Ordered a burrito and burrito bowl off of GOJEK delivery from here and the resturant literally doubled the price on us. The driver gave us the receipt. 

The burrito bowl was super tiny and the burrito was soggy and flavorless. Save yourself the trouble

Great restaurant! 
Extremely fresh food and staff is really cool!
One of my favorites in Bali!
Setting was a bit rural but they had very good food for a good price. Both of us ordered chicken quesadilla :)

It was terrible. The carne (beef) nachos was basically a tasteless bit of diced stesk on top of deep fried oily corn chips topped with salad and a bit of avocado and beans. All the ingredients were correct but there was no taste and no love. Staff were good and the prices were low but deservedly so. Definately won't go back. My husband had the tacos which were exactly the same but in a different shell. We both left 90% of our meal on our plates. One positive was the beer was really cold.

Ordered via delivery. Price was literally double what was stated via go food and driver had no invoice. I can understand small differences but this was a joke. Burrito was terrible with no guac or sour cream, 90% rice. Tried calling the number to query the price difference but it's not in service. Avoid this scam restaurant and get great burritos at taco beach or lacalaca.
